  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "SALVAGE ENGINEER",
  "description": "<p>Salvage Engineer Responsibilities & Duties</p><ul><li>Develop and implement salvage plans for sunken or damaged vessels.</li></ul><ul><li>Conduct thorough inspections and assessments of underwater wrecks.</li></ul><ul><li>Coordinate and oversee diving operations during salvage missions.</li></ul><ul><li>Operate and maintain specialized salvage equipment such as cranes and lifting bags.</li></ul><ul><li>Ensure adherence to safety protocols and environmental regulations.</li></ul><ul><li>Collaborate with naval architects to design structural reinforcements for recovery missions.</li></ul><ul><li>Prepare technical reports and documentation on salvage activities.</li></ul><ul><li>Analyze and mitigate risks associated with salvage operations.</li></ul><ul><li>Manage logistics and resource allocation for salvage projects.</li></ul><ul><li>Provide training and guidance to junior salvage team members.</li></ul><p><br /><strong>Requirements</strong></p><ul><li>Bachelor’s degree in Engineering with Relevant work experience in a related field (or) Rich Experience in related filed with basic Qualification.</li></ul><ul><li>Extensive experience in marine salvage operations.</li></ul><ul><li>Strong leadership and project management skills.</li></ul><ul><li>Proficiency in computer-aided design (CAD) software.</li></ul><ul><li>Experience with underwater robotics and remote-operated vehicles (ROVs).</li></ul><ul><li>Thorough knowledge of international marine laws and environmental regulations.</li></ul><ul><li>Minimum of 4-5 years of experience in marine engineering or salvage operations.</li></ul><ul><li>Strong analytical and problem-solving skills.</li></ul><ul><li>Excellent communication and teamwork abilities.</li></ul><ul><li>Proven ability to work in high-pressure and hazardous environments.</li></ul><ul><li>Willingness to travel and work irregular hours.</li></ul><ul><li>Valid certification in basic and advanced diving techniques.</li></ul><ul><li>Proficiency in using specialized salvage and marine equipment.</li></ul><p><strong>Only shortlisted candidate will be notified</strong></p>",
